column1: Data Supplied By: National Livestock Reporting Service
Data source: National Livestock Reporting Service
Please see terms of use here: https://www.mla.com.au/general/Terms-and-conditions/data-and-information/

Numbers were down for a total yarding of 1347 mainly good quality weaner calves. Steer calf numbers were dominated by heavy weights with prices trending up 5c/kg. Lighter weight steer calves eased on last week with background and restocker buyers selective. Heavy weight heifer calves gained with demand while medium weights remained firm and light weight heifers eased 10c/kg.

Weaner steers weighing over 380kg sold from 290c to 344c while weights from 330 to 380kg made 264c to 350c and lighter weights under 330kg returned 262c to 336c quality dependent.

Weaner heifers weighing over 380kg reached 258c to 282c while weights from 330kg to 380kg sold from 242c to 284c /kg. Lighter weight calves under 330kg made from 140c to 268c /kg.

Tracey Kilner--NLRS
